<subSubSection id="C31F6781D714FFDE81D7FB56893D5A13" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD714FFDE81D7FB568E405A53" blockId="2.[166,1225,1210,1396]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">
C o l o r a t i o n. F e m a l e. Generally body colour as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D714FFDE8266FB568E505BB3" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[874,1098,1210,1236]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persuasoria">
<emphasis id="B971E818D714FFDE8266FB568E505BB3" box="[874,1098,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Rhyssa persuasoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but white marks more abundant: face sometimes almost white, with only a black central spot, band on flagellum (central flagellomeres) white. Clypeus, coxae partly, trochanters and trochantelli usually yellow. Head and propodeum often with red coloration in the dark areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD714FFDE81D7FAD6893D5A13" blockId="2.[166,1225,1210,1396]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">M a l e. Body colour as in female, but face entirely, fore and mid coxae, trochanters and trochantelli entirely, scape and pedicel dorsally yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF7A6482D714FFDE81AAF9058909584E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403921" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6403921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403921/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" startId="2.[166,199,1769,1791]" targetBox="[166,1225,1420,1747]" targetPageId="2">
